revision.text:
{{italic title}}
[[File:A short biographical dictionary of English literature, title 2.jpeg|thumb|right|Title page]]
'''''A Short Biographical Dictionary of English Literature''''' is a collection of biographies of writers by [[John William Cousin]] (1849–1910), published in 1910. Most of the entries consist of only one paragraph but some entries, like [[William Shakespeare]]'s, are quite lengthy.<ref>[[s:A Short Biographical Dictionary of English Literature|''A Short Biographical Dictionary of English Literature'']], [[John William Cousin]] (1849–1910), published in 1910</ref>

The book was the 5,000th [[e-book]] provided by the [[Distributed Proofreaders]] project to [[Project Gutenberg]], where it was released on August 21, 2004.

